4.text_en:
Section 4. In this Act:
'Investment promotion' means the promotion of investment in any of the activities designated by the Board;
'Promoted person' means a person to whom a promotion certificate has been granted;
'Promotion certificate' means a certificate granted by the Board to any person for the purpose of investment promotion;
'Board' means the Board of Investment.

27.text_en:
Section 27. A promoted person shall be permitted to own land for carrying on the promoted activity to such extent as the Board deems appropriate, notwithstanding the provisions of any other law.
The ownership of land under paragraph one shall be subject to the following conditions:
(1) The land must be used for the purposes specified in the promotion certificate;
(2) The promoted person must maintain a paid-up registered capital of not less than the amount prescribed in the Ministerial Regulation;
(3) Other conditions as prescribed by the Board.
